record.recordid: Print Start command panel - print.start - en
record.format.name: print.start

brief.brief: The Print.Start command panel enables you to start up the print routine.

detail.detail: Spool File: (file variable) Specify the spool file variable.
Report Name: (character) Specify the name of the report, if any.
Scheduled Printer: (character) Specify the printer, if any.
Printer Class: (character) Specify the printer class, if any.
Forms Class: (character) Specify the forms class, if any.
Priority: (number) Specify the priority, if any.
Number of Copies: (number) Specify the number of copies, if any.
Delete after Printing: (Boolean) Specify whether to delete after printing. Specify true to delete.
Spoolheader File: (file variable) Specify the spoolheader file variable.
Before you do a print, you must do a print.start panel.
